WEBVTT

00:00:02.720 --> 00:00:05.518
- <i>Previously on</i> The O.C.<i>:</i>
- I can't do this anymore. I don't trust you.

00:00:05.680 --> 00:00:06.908
Oliver's not stable. He's dangerous.

00:00:07.080 --> 00:00:09.674
Oliver has not done anything to Marissa
except be her friend.

00:00:09.840 --> 00:00:12.149
Look, you guys may not believe me.
No one may believe me.

00:00:12.320 --> 00:00:13.435
- Theresa.
- Ryan Atwood.

00:00:13.600 --> 00:00:15.591
- So you two were...
- We grew up together.

00:00:16.520 --> 00:00:18.078
I always had a crush on you.

00:00:19.080 --> 00:00:20.069
You should go.

00:00:20.240 --> 00:00:22.708
I'm not gonna stand here and pretend
like I'm your girlfriend when I'm not.

00:00:22.920 --> 00:00:23.909
At least not anymore.

00:00:24.080 --> 00:00:26.310
Put the gun down,
you get a second chance.

00:00:26.480 --> 00:00:30.519
- I'm sorry. You were right.
- It's okay. It's okay.

00:00:43.360 --> 00:00:46.557
Happy Valentine's Day.
Someone just got struck by cupid's arrow.

00:00:47.160 --> 00:00:49.196
Happy Valentine's Day.

00:00:50.560 --> 00:00:53.438
- Valentine's Day's not till tomorrow.
- You're not excited?

00:00:53.600 --> 00:00:57.718
I am. I am. I'm just still thinking
about Oliver with that gun.

00:00:57.880 --> 00:00:59.836
- I know.
- Who knows what could've happened?

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:02.514
But it didn't.
And Dr. Kim lifted Ryan's suspension.

00:01:02.680 --> 00:01:05.433
So the best thing is for
everything to return to normal.

00:01:05.600 --> 00:01:08.637
And in this house that means
celebrating the holidays.

00:01:08.800 --> 00:01:11.837
Valentine's Day is not a holiday.
Rosh Hashanah, that's a holiday.

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:15.549
Memorial Day? Yes, a holiday.
You know who invented Valentine's Day?

00:01:15.720 --> 00:01:17.631
- St. Valentine.
- Hershey's and Hallmark.

00:01:17.800 --> 00:01:19.392
If you're single, it depresses you.

00:01:19.560 --> 00:01:22.199
If you are in love, start shelling out.
Chocolate. Flowers.

00:01:22.360 --> 00:01:24.157
- Lingerie.
- You never bought me lingerie.

00:01:24.320 --> 00:01:26.276
See how upset you are?
I hate this holiday.

00:01:26.440 --> 00:01:29.000
- Must be talking about Valentine's Day.
- I am. I hate it.

00:01:31.680 --> 00:01:34.956
- Hey. You got me.
- Guess who got shot by cupid's arrow.

00:01:35.120 --> 00:01:36.348
Is someone going overboard?

00:01:36.520 --> 00:01:38.431
You're one to talk.
Chrismukkah, anyone?

00:01:38.600 --> 00:01:41.194
- At least that's a real holiday.
- Tell her, Dad. It's two.

00:01:41.360 --> 00:01:43.828
- Seth made that word up when he was 6.
- It's an important...

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:46.355
This is an important holiday.
It's Valentine's Day.

00:01:46.520 --> 00:01:49.318
- Where Jewishness fuses with Christianity.
- Do the math.

00:01:55.680 --> 00:01:58.752
- How you doing, kid?
- You know. Okay, I guess.

00:01:58.920 --> 00:02:03.357
You're about to be great. Tomorrow
is the big Valentine's Day Singles' Gala.

00:02:03.520 --> 00:02:05.715
A benefit for Newport Memorial's
Heart Department.

00:02:05.880 --> 00:02:09.236
Big party. You guys are gonna dress up.
Everyone's gonna be there.

00:02:09.400 --> 00:02:12.836
Just like normal, huh? Yes!

00:02:18.160 --> 00:02:19.149
I'm gonna go.

00:03:00.640 --> 00:03:03.359
- Ryan. Hey.
- Hey.

00:03:09.280 --> 00:03:10.679
Were you able to sleep at all?

00:03:10.840 --> 00:03:12.159
- Not much.
- Me either.

00:03:12.320 --> 00:03:14.880
- I kept going over everything in my head.
- Yeah.

00:03:15.040 --> 00:03:17.793
He's in the hospital,
so hopefully he'll get better.

00:03:17.960 --> 00:03:19.359
I hope so.

00:03:19.520 --> 00:03:23.513
I'm ready for everything to just
go back to normal. The way it was.

00:03:26.400 --> 00:03:29.631
Great. So, Valentine's Day tomorrow.

00:03:29.800 --> 00:03:31.916
- Yeah?
- What were you gonna do? Because...

00:03:32.080 --> 00:03:34.116
...I didn't know if you wanted to...
- Yeah, no.

00:03:34.280 --> 00:03:36.874
- Kirsten's hosting this singles' dance...
- For the hospital.

00:03:37.040 --> 00:03:39.110
I told her I'd go.
I didn't know if you wanted...

00:03:39.280 --> 00:03:40.554
Of course.

00:03:41.640 --> 00:03:44.393
Right. Well, then I'll go too.

00:03:45.920 --> 00:03:48.195
Who knows?
Maybe we'll meet somebody there.

00:03:48.360 --> 00:03:49.793
Yeah. Who knows?

00:03:53.760 --> 00:03:58.390
- All right. I should get to...
- Yeah. No. Me too.

00:04:17.760 --> 00:04:18.909
Hey, Summer.

00:04:19.080 --> 00:04:20.752
God, Cohen. You made me mess up.

00:04:20.920 --> 00:04:23.912
- I'm going for the high score.
- Hey, it's good to see you too.

00:04:24.080 --> 00:04:26.719
- Tomorrow's Valentine's Day.
- Oh, really?

00:04:26.880 --> 00:04:29.269
God. I didn't know tomorrow
was Valentine's Day.

00:04:29.440 --> 00:04:32.352
But thanks for reminding me.
Have fun with Anna.

00:04:32.520 --> 00:04:35.114
- Anna's in Pittsburgh for the weekend.
- On Valentine's Day?

00:04:35.280 --> 00:04:36.918
Hey, now that's commitment.

00:04:37.440 --> 00:04:40.716
Actually, Anna and I broke up.

00:04:40.920 --> 00:04:43.150
And I wanted to see
what you're doing tomorrow.

00:04:47.320 --> 00:04:49.276
- So you guys broke up.
- Yeah.

00:04:49.440 --> 00:04:53.353
Coffee. You're single now and you want
to know what I'm doing for Valentine's.

00:04:53.520 --> 00:04:55.078
- Yeah.
- So Anna dumps you...

00:04:55.240 --> 00:04:58.471
...and you think you can choose me
and I'd still be interested in you?

00:04:58.640 --> 00:05:01.757
First of all, what makes you think
that Anna dumped me?

00:05:01.920 --> 00:05:03.990
Never mind. Second of all...

00:05:04.480 --> 00:05:07.790
...kind of. Yes.
- Yeah. No. No way.

00:05:07.960 --> 00:05:10.110
I'm not gonna be your
sloppy seconds, ass-face.

00:05:10.400 --> 00:05:12.994
Besides, I'm busy tomorrow.
I'll be at the singles' dance.

00:05:13.160 --> 00:05:14.673
- So will I.
- I don't care.

00:05:14.840 --> 00:05:15.989
- See you there.
- Not if I see you first.

00:05:16.160 --> 00:05:19.835
- Maybe we'll both meet someone special.
- Yeah, as long as his name isn't Cohen.

00:05:21.680 --> 00:05:23.352
Snap.

00:05:25.600 --> 00:05:26.715
I'm sorry I'm late.

00:05:26.880 --> 00:05:29.758
Crusading for the rich and dysfunctional
is time-consuming.

00:05:29.920 --> 00:05:31.911
Let me just dot my I's and cross my T's.

00:05:32.080 --> 00:05:35.516
Come on, I'm starving. I've been thinking
about crab cakes for the last hour.

00:05:35.680 --> 00:05:37.591
Will you be around tomorrow
to help set up?

00:05:37.920 --> 00:05:40.593
- For what?
- The Valentine's Day Single Dance Gala.

00:05:40.760 --> 00:05:43.832
No. I can't do it.
I got this petty nuisance lawsuit. In fact...

00:05:44.440 --> 00:05:46.396
...I'm pretty booked this weekend.

00:05:46.560 --> 00:05:50.872
So I might be a little late to
the Valentine's Day Dance Singles' Gala.

00:05:51.040 --> 00:05:52.758
- Singles.
- Singles' Dance Gala.

00:05:53.280 --> 00:05:54.429
Why?

00:05:54.600 --> 00:05:56.909
- We said we'd go together.
- It's restaurant stuff.

00:05:57.080 --> 00:05:59.992
Got the zoning inspectors coming by
before we can expand the deck.

00:06:00.160 --> 00:06:02.754
- On Saturday?
- I guess these city council guys are busy.

00:06:02.920 --> 00:06:05.150
- No. I forbid it.
- You what?

00:06:05.320 --> 00:06:07.629
With whatever wifely authority
I have vested in me...

00:06:07.800 --> 00:06:10.234
...on this most holy
and romantic of days, no.

00:06:10.400 --> 00:06:14.837
- It's only a holiday. Not even a real one.
- Not this again. Not on an empty stomach.

00:06:15.000 --> 00:06:18.470
How about Arbor Day? Trees?
That's a good cause. Or Secretary's Day.

00:06:18.640 --> 00:06:21.393
- How about our anniversary?
- Which we might not make it to.

00:06:21.560 --> 00:06:23.630
You know you'll have more fun
without me.

00:06:23.800 --> 00:06:26.837
No. You're going.
Sandy, this is important to me.

00:06:27.000 --> 00:06:29.434
There's a lot of things
important to me that you don't do.

00:06:29.600 --> 00:06:30.794
- Like what?
- Like golfing.

00:06:30.960 --> 00:06:33.793
- Lots of couples golf together.
- Shortly before dying of old age.

00:06:33.960 --> 00:06:36.428
Surfing. How often have I tried
to get you in the ocean?

00:06:36.600 --> 00:06:39.637
- With the fish?
- And still I'm patient. I'm forgiving.

00:06:39.840 --> 00:06:41.876
- You're joking.
- I put up with your father.

00:06:42.040 --> 00:06:45.350
- You're eligible for sainthood any day.
- I forgive your snoring.

00:06:45.520 --> 00:06:47.988
- I do not snore.
- Yeah, you do.

00:06:48.160 --> 00:06:50.230
Like a freight train
roaring through the house.

00:06:50.400 --> 00:06:52.436
You wanted to do this restaurant,
I supported you.

00:06:52.600 --> 00:06:56.149
You wanted to go into private practice,
who had your back?

00:06:56.320 --> 00:06:59.630
- I put up with your father.
- You never wanna do anything I like.

00:06:59.800 --> 00:07:01.438
Everything's a fight, an argument.

00:07:01.600 --> 00:07:04.637
- My life, my job.
- Yeah, yeah, yeah, and I'm still here.

00:07:04.800 --> 00:07:06.552
- Don't do me any favors.
- I won't.

00:07:06.720 --> 00:07:08.119
- Fine.
- Perfect.

00:07:08.960 --> 00:07:10.837
- What are we fighting about?
- I'm not sure.

00:07:11.000 --> 00:07:12.319
But it's serious.

00:07:12.680 --> 00:07:15.069
You're on your own for lunch.

00:07:16.120 --> 00:07:17.792
Happy Valentine's Day.

00:07:22.640 --> 00:07:24.790
Hey, kiddo.

00:07:25.240 --> 00:07:28.277
Plasterer came to the restaurant today.
Made a total mess.

00:07:28.440 --> 00:07:30.396
But progress is being made.

00:07:30.560 --> 00:07:32.835
- How's school?
- Okay.

00:07:33.000 --> 00:07:34.831
- Yeah?
- Hey, you got something.

00:07:35.000 --> 00:07:37.150
It was left for you at the door.

00:07:38.840 --> 00:07:42.913
Well, it's not ticking,
so it can't be from your mom.

00:07:43.760 --> 00:07:45.955
"Hope you're not too Ionely
this Valentine's Day.

00:07:46.120 --> 00:07:48.953
X O, X O. Your Secret Admirer."

00:07:49.120 --> 00:07:51.998
Marissa, you're so sweet.
You didn't have to do that.

00:07:52.160 --> 00:07:54.276
- I didn't.
- Well...

00:07:54.440 --> 00:07:57.079
...who else would've left something nice?
- Good question.

00:07:57.360 --> 00:08:00.557
This year I'm doing my best
to avoid Valentine's Day completely.

00:08:01.000 --> 00:08:05.118
- What? You and Ryan are...?
- I don't really want to talk about it.

00:08:05.280 --> 00:08:09.398
- And neither does he.
- Well, it is Valentine's Day.

00:08:09.560 --> 00:08:14.475
Sometimes the big romantic gesture
is more effective than talking.

00:08:16.160 --> 00:08:18.674
There's no way your mom
gave me these, right? No.

00:08:18.840 --> 00:08:22.037
She doesn't make her disdain for me
a secret. Much less her admiration.

00:08:22.200 --> 00:08:24.031
Well, have you kissed anyone recently?

00:08:25.280 --> 00:08:26.998
<i>Previously on</i> The Valley:

00:08:27.160 --> 00:08:29.594
<i>I just don 't feel like I fit</i>
<i>here in Tarzana.</i>

00:08:29.760 --> 00:08:31.432
I'm busy. Studying...

00:08:31.600 --> 00:08:33.318
...naked.

00:08:33.480 --> 00:08:36.074
Is that supposed to keep me away?

00:08:36.600 --> 00:08:38.238
Cohen?

00:08:41.200 --> 00:08:43.236
- You're at my house.
- And you're dressed.

00:08:43.400 --> 00:08:45.675
I wonder who's more disappointed.

00:08:46.120 --> 00:08:47.109
- Can I come in?
- No.

00:08:47.280 --> 00:08:48.315
Thanks.

00:08:49.240 --> 00:08:51.196
What are you doing here?

00:08:52.960 --> 00:08:54.109
Who's this?

00:08:54.280 --> 00:08:55.599
- No one.
- "I'm not no one."

00:08:55.760 --> 00:08:58.228
- Princess Sparkle. What do you want?
- She's Captain Oats' type.

00:08:58.400 --> 00:09:00.709
You tell him to keep his hooves off.
As for you...

00:09:00.880 --> 00:09:04.873
Wait, wait. Before you kick me out, can
you please give me a second to explain?

00:09:06.320 --> 00:09:08.550
Okay, listen. Summer...

00:09:10.240 --> 00:09:12.515
...it's not like...

00:09:12.680 --> 00:09:15.831
...now that me and Anna broke up
I'm now choosing you.

00:09:16.000 --> 00:09:17.592
Okay?

00:09:19.040 --> 00:09:22.476
Because the whole reason
that we broke up...

00:09:22.640 --> 00:09:24.676
...is because for me...

00:09:27.000 --> 00:09:29.434
...it's always been you, Summer.

00:09:29.600 --> 00:09:31.352
It's always been you.

00:09:31.520 --> 00:09:33.988
I've tried to fight it,
and I've tried to deny it.

00:09:34.160 --> 00:09:36.799
And I can't. I can't do it.

00:09:36.960 --> 00:09:38.871
You're undeniable.

00:09:54.720 --> 00:09:56.756
- Cohen?
- Yeah.

00:09:56.920 --> 00:09:58.638
Do you happen...

00:09:59.560 --> 00:10:01.357
...to have...

00:10:01.520 --> 00:10:03.476
...you know...?
- Oh...

00:10:04.520 --> 00:10:07.114
...yeah, I do. In my wallet.
- Yeah?

00:10:07.280 --> 00:10:11.353
I was beginning to view it as sort of
a rabbit's foot, for good luck only, but...

00:10:11.520 --> 00:10:13.750
You're about to get lucky.

00:10:20.600 --> 00:10:22.989
Whatever you say, Summer. Yes.

00:10:23.320 --> 00:10:24.992
Yes.

00:10:40.000 --> 00:10:42.309
- Luke. Hi.
- Hi, Mrs. Cooper.

00:10:43.040 --> 00:10:44.837
What are you doing here?

00:10:48.160 --> 00:10:51.755
Do you know...? I was wondering,
did Marissa bring her bio textbook home?

00:10:51.920 --> 00:10:55.071
Marissa doesn't live here anymore, Luke.
You know that.

00:10:55.280 --> 00:10:57.714
Right. I must have forgot.

00:11:00.160 --> 00:11:02.549
Right. Okay. Well, good night.

00:11:03.200 --> 00:11:07.637
Tomorrow is the Valentine's Day party.
Are you gonna go?

00:11:07.800 --> 00:11:11.588
Because I'm gonna go.
And I thought if you needed a ride...

00:11:12.320 --> 00:11:14.788
Actually, everything that's happened
with Caleb and me...

00:11:14.960 --> 00:11:17.269
...I think it's best I stay home.
Avoid this holiday.

00:11:17.440 --> 00:11:18.714
Yeah.

00:11:18.880 --> 00:11:21.110
It's just another day of the week, right?

00:11:23.200 --> 00:11:25.077
Okay.

00:11:25.240 --> 00:11:28.312
- Good night, Mrs. Cooper.
- Good night.

00:11:40.720 --> 00:11:42.199
So...

00:11:42.360 --> 00:11:44.157
...that was sex.

00:11:44.640 --> 00:11:46.232
Yep.

00:11:47.680 --> 00:11:50.274
- I'm gonna go.
- Me too.

00:11:50.440 --> 00:11:51.839
But you live here.

00:11:52.000 --> 00:11:53.911
I meant downstairs.

00:11:54.080 --> 00:11:55.399
Okay.

00:11:55.560 --> 00:11:57.152
Perfect.

00:12:17.680 --> 00:12:19.113
Hi.

00:12:27.200 --> 00:12:29.430
I love you so much.

00:12:31.880 --> 00:12:34.394
We've waited a long time to...

00:12:34.560 --> 00:12:39.873
...you know, and I thought maybe
we could start Valentine's Day early.

00:12:43.200 --> 00:12:45.760
- No. Wait. Wait. Hold on.
- What?

00:12:45.920 --> 00:12:47.638
Don't you want to?

00:12:47.800 --> 00:12:49.233
No.

00:12:51.160 --> 00:12:52.798
No. I mean, yeah.

00:12:52.960 --> 00:12:54.473
Yeah, of course.

00:12:55.200 --> 00:12:57.760
But with everything that's happened,
it just...

00:12:57.920 --> 00:13:01.151
- It seems a little soon.
- I just wish it hadn't happened.

00:13:01.320 --> 00:13:03.959
That we could still be like we were...

00:13:05.520 --> 00:13:08.671
...and I wanted to make it up to you.
- You don't have to...

00:13:08.840 --> 00:13:10.717
...do this.

00:13:11.560 --> 00:13:13.357
No. You're right.

00:13:13.520 --> 00:13:16.876
So I guess I'll go.

00:13:17.040 --> 00:13:19.076
- Because this is just really...
- Wrong?

00:13:20.040 --> 00:13:22.873
I was gonna say "embarrassing."
But I guess "wrong" works.

00:13:23.040 --> 00:13:28.398
So it was nice to see you.
And I guess I'll see you again tomorrow.

00:13:40.680 --> 00:13:44.753
- Hey, buddy. Got some big news.
- I was about to go set up. You coming?

00:13:44.920 --> 00:13:46.751
It's a lot of lifting. It's not my thing.

00:13:46.920 --> 00:13:49.832
I don't know if I just mentioned this,
but I have some big news.

00:13:50.000 --> 00:13:52.992
- Yeah, so I heard. What's up?
- Ryan, I'm a man now.

00:13:53.160 --> 00:13:56.197
Not just like an after-your-bar-mitzvah
man, but a "man" man.

00:13:56.360 --> 00:14:00.114
I had sex with a girl.
Summer, to be more specific.

00:14:00.280 --> 00:14:02.157
How was it?

00:14:02.760 --> 00:14:04.318
- I had sex.
- That bad?

00:14:04.880 --> 00:14:07.792
No, not that bad...

00:14:07.960 --> 00:14:09.951
...just kind of weird.
- Weird?

00:14:10.120 --> 00:14:13.635
Yeah, but not kinky weird.
More like weird awkward.

00:14:13.800 --> 00:14:16.678
But, hey, it was my first time.
She's a more experienced woman.

00:14:16.840 --> 00:14:17.989
That's to be expected.

00:14:18.160 --> 00:14:22.790
And I did make some faces in the middle
that I wish I could take back, but I can't.

00:14:22.960 --> 00:14:26.396
There was also sort of a whiny noise
that came out towards the end...

00:14:26.840 --> 00:14:30.355
...that probably wasn't my finest hour.
I sucked so bad.

00:14:30.520 --> 00:14:33.273
I was like a fish flopping around
on dry land.

00:14:33.440 --> 00:14:37.319
Ryan, I was Nemo.
And I just wanted to go home.

00:14:37.560 --> 00:14:41.314
- Don't worry. You'll get another chance.
- That's the thing. I'm not sure I will.

00:14:41.480 --> 00:14:45.792
The situation with Summer is murkier now
than it was before the awful fish sex.

00:14:45.960 --> 00:14:47.518
I wouldn't refer to it as fish sex.

00:14:47.680 --> 00:14:50.558
Good point. That's something
I was hoping to get more of: Tips.

00:14:50.720 --> 00:14:54.030
Tricks of the trade. Summer's used to
driving a higher performance vehicle.

00:14:54.200 --> 00:14:56.430
Don't know if I'm the guy
to talk to about romance.

00:14:56.600 --> 00:14:57.794
- Why?
- Me and Marissa.

00:14:57.960 --> 00:15:00.872
- It's different now, post-Oliver.
- Yeah? You wanna talk about it?

00:15:01.040 --> 00:15:03.395
- No, I should get over to set up.
- Hey.

00:15:03.560 --> 00:15:05.630
So do you have tips
or words of wisdom for me?

00:15:05.800 --> 00:15:07.279
Do it again.

00:15:08.480 --> 00:15:10.710
That's what I was afraid of.

00:15:12.840 --> 00:15:17.436
And then we both just decided to wait.
Because, you know, we were really tired.

00:15:17.600 --> 00:15:19.477
Well, you know how it goes.

00:15:22.280 --> 00:15:25.078
- I wish we had waited.
- What? Who?

00:15:25.640 --> 00:15:27.517
Me and Cohen.

00:15:27.800 --> 00:15:29.836
- We had sex.
- Wait, what?

00:15:30.200 --> 00:15:31.679
You guys did what?

