00:31:48.080 --> 00:31:52.392
- You know, the thing about Ryan...
- No, this isn't...

00:31:52.720 --> 00:31:54.711
- It's not... I'm fine.
- I know.

00:31:54.880 --> 00:31:58.953
But the thing about Ryan is,
whenever things have gotten tough...

00:31:59.120 --> 00:32:02.157
...everyone in his life has abandoned him.
- That's what he thinks I did.

00:32:02.320 --> 00:32:03.719
Surprise him. Show him you didn't.

00:32:04.080 --> 00:32:06.514
- That you're not gonna give up on him.
- He wants me to.

00:32:06.680 --> 00:32:09.990
Well, only because he expects you to.
It's crazy.

00:32:10.320 --> 00:32:11.514
Love is crazy.

00:32:11.680 --> 00:32:14.319
It's always challenging. It's never easy.

00:32:14.480 --> 00:32:17.278
- Yeah, but is it always this hard?
- Sometimes.

00:32:17.440 --> 00:32:19.431
But you hang in there anyway.

00:32:19.600 --> 00:32:21.795
If you're having the worst fight
in the world...

00:32:21.960 --> 00:32:25.748
...or some stupid argument that neither
of you can remember what it's about.

00:32:25.920 --> 00:32:27.592
Because it's...

00:32:27.760 --> 00:32:29.512
It's worth it.

00:32:31.480 --> 00:32:33.596
You guys have been
through so much already.

00:32:34.000 --> 00:32:35.911
Why quit now?

00:32:38.800 --> 00:32:40.438
- Hey, Mr. Cohen.
- Hello, Summer.

00:32:40.600 --> 00:32:43.353
- Hi. Coop, you ready to go?
- Yeah.

00:32:43.520 --> 00:32:45.829
- You okay, kiddo?
- Yeah. Thanks.

00:32:54.200 --> 00:32:57.556
- Sometimes you make it hard to hate you.
- I know.

00:32:57.720 --> 00:33:00.712
It's all... It's all... It's part of my charm.

00:33:00.880 --> 00:33:03.189
Sometimes you make it easy.

00:33:05.080 --> 00:33:08.629
- Charming too, no?
- Let's go home.

00:33:29.760 --> 00:33:32.194
You tried to jump that fence
and your pants got caught.

00:33:32.360 --> 00:33:33.509
I was pretty graceful.

00:33:33.680 --> 00:33:36.911
- Yeah, especially when you face-planted.
- Glad to see you enjoy my pain.

00:33:37.080 --> 00:33:39.833
We had no ice and we had to use
that bag of frozen peas.

00:33:40.000 --> 00:33:43.197
Yeah. Frozen vegetables.
The miracle cure.

00:33:45.560 --> 00:33:49.075
It's pretty amazing, us running into
each other on Valentine's Day.

00:33:52.360 --> 00:33:55.033
I gotta get back. Help clean up.

00:33:56.400 --> 00:33:59.198
So do you go to a lot
of these kinds of events?

00:34:00.200 --> 00:34:02.236
Pretty much every week.

00:34:02.760 --> 00:34:05.433
Well, then maybe I'll run into you again.

00:34:06.280 --> 00:34:08.794
Plus, I know where you live.

00:34:14.320 --> 00:34:16.959
- Oh, God.
- I know I shouldn't be here.

00:34:17.280 --> 00:34:19.714
- No, you shouldn't, Luke.
- But it's just...

00:34:19.880 --> 00:34:21.871
I don't know,
you looked so sad when you left.

00:34:22.040 --> 00:34:25.350
I couldn't bear the thought of you
being alone on Valentine's Day.

00:34:25.520 --> 00:34:28.034
Most people would enjoy that thought.

00:34:28.200 --> 00:34:29.758
Not me.

00:34:30.600 --> 00:34:33.990
Mrs. Cooper, you are an amazing girl.

00:34:35.480 --> 00:34:36.913
Woman.

00:34:37.400 --> 00:34:38.913
Lady.

00:34:39.280 --> 00:34:42.556
- Lf Mr. Nichol doesn't appreciate you...
- No. He sure doesn't.

00:34:42.720 --> 00:34:46.554
That's because he's too old to see
what he's lucky enough to have.

00:34:49.400 --> 00:34:53.393
And you should also know that
you have always been the coolest mom.

00:34:53.600 --> 00:34:55.716
- Luke.
- It's true. You let us listen to...

00:34:55.880 --> 00:35:00.271
...whatever we wanted to in the carpool.
And you let us watch R-rated movies.

00:35:00.440 --> 00:35:05.036
- And whenever we played Ultimatum...
- Ultimatum?

00:35:06.280 --> 00:35:10.956
You know, who, of all your
friends' moms, would you rather do?

00:35:12.000 --> 00:35:14.912
- That's a game?
- And whenever we played it...

00:35:15.080 --> 00:35:18.197
...you always won.
- Really?

00:35:18.760 --> 00:35:21.593
- I beat Kirsten?
- I thought you should know the truth...

00:35:21.760 --> 00:35:23.796
...on Valentine's Day.

00:35:26.280 --> 00:35:27.918
- Good night.
- Wait.

00:35:40.640 --> 00:35:41.868
Thank you.

00:36:06.280 --> 00:36:08.191
Would you like to come in?

00:36:16.680 --> 00:36:19.717
I guess you're happy that today is over.

00:36:19.880 --> 00:36:21.711
Absolutely.

00:36:30.080 --> 00:36:32.674
Oh, my God, Sandy.

00:36:32.960 --> 00:36:36.316
Somebody's got to keep
Hershey's and Hallmark in business.

00:36:44.000 --> 00:36:46.719
- So you want to be my Valentine?
- Yes.

00:36:46.880 --> 00:36:51.237
Just as soon as I have some of these
caramel chocolates. They're my favorite.

00:36:51.400 --> 00:36:54.039
The square ones.
I like the ones with nuts.

00:36:55.880 --> 00:36:59.668
Not to rub it in, man,
but I think Princess Sparkle is your type.

00:36:59.920 --> 00:37:02.115
Yeah, I blew it for us both.

00:37:02.440 --> 00:37:03.589
What's that?

00:37:03.760 --> 00:37:05.591
Yeah. Are you kidding?
Great hooves.

00:37:06.960 --> 00:37:09.520
- Cohen?
- Summer.

00:37:09.680 --> 00:37:11.511
- Hey.
- Hey.

00:37:14.480 --> 00:37:15.879
No.

00:37:18.920 --> 00:37:20.558
The other night...

00:37:21.320 --> 00:37:22.878
...when we...

00:37:23.360 --> 00:37:26.113
...had sex.
- Yeah.

00:37:27.680 --> 00:37:29.875
You weren't the only virgin in the room.

00:37:30.480 --> 00:37:32.789
There was someone else in the room?
Like, filming us?

00:37:32.960 --> 00:37:34.837
Me, jackass.

00:37:35.160 --> 00:37:37.469
I'm a virgin.

00:37:37.640 --> 00:37:40.029
Or I was a virgin.

00:37:42.640 --> 00:37:44.517
Why didn't you tell me?

00:37:44.680 --> 00:37:46.716
I don't know.

00:37:46.960 --> 00:37:51.556
I guess I felt like
I had this reputation to uphold...

00:37:52.040 --> 00:37:55.112
...and I figured you'd think less of me.
- No.

00:37:55.400 --> 00:37:59.075
Are you kidding? Not at all.
I'm just... I'm shocked.

00:37:59.640 --> 00:38:04.236
God. Never in a million years would I
think that you, of all people, not that...

00:38:04.400 --> 00:38:06.755
That is not what's important here.

00:38:08.000 --> 00:38:10.753
This was a huge moment in our lives
and we just blew past it.

00:38:10.920 --> 00:38:12.876
- Really quickly.
- Hey, not that quickly.

00:38:14.240 --> 00:38:16.196
Pretty quickly, yes.

00:38:17.360 --> 00:38:19.078
And it was a big deal.

00:38:19.240 --> 00:38:22.357
I think that it should've been special.

00:38:22.520 --> 00:38:24.397
And we rushed it.

00:38:26.760 --> 00:38:28.796
What if...

00:38:29.320 --> 00:38:31.709
...we were to slow it down a little bit?

00:38:32.320 --> 00:38:34.276
Maybe...

00:38:34.640 --> 00:38:36.676
...start from the beginning?

00:38:37.160 --> 00:38:38.752
What do you mean?

00:38:52.200 --> 00:38:55.909
- You are so cheesy, Cohen.
- Come on.

00:38:56.080 --> 00:38:58.275
I'm sweeping you off your feet.

00:38:59.720 --> 00:39:03.156
Well, the sad part is...

00:39:04.120 --> 00:39:05.997
...you kind of are.

00:39:37.240 --> 00:39:39.151
- Where is she?
- What?

00:39:39.320 --> 00:39:42.995
Theresa. If she's here, I want her
to know I'm not gonna lose you.

00:39:43.160 --> 00:39:45.230
I'm not gonna give up on you.

00:39:45.400 --> 00:39:47.197
She left.

00:39:48.320 --> 00:39:51.392
- I'm so sorry.
- I know.

00:39:59.640 --> 00:40:01.835
Can't you just forgive me?

00:40:02.960 --> 00:40:04.359
How?

00:40:07.440 --> 00:40:09.317
I don't know...

00:40:10.240 --> 00:40:12.276
...if we should be together.

00:40:13.280 --> 00:40:18.434
I mean, look how easy it was for someone
to come into our lives, come between us.

00:40:20.640 --> 00:40:23.438
- How do I know it won't happen again?
- It won't.

00:40:23.600 --> 00:40:26.068
- You have to trust me.
- Like you trusted me.

00:40:27.760 --> 00:40:29.318
Ryan.

00:40:32.960 --> 00:40:34.393
So that's it?

00:40:37.080 --> 00:40:39.548
I can't pretend it didn't happen.

00:00:0.500 --> 00:00:2.00
